H0.text: Food chain is the pattern represented by trees starting as seeds and growing into mature trees that produce more seeds.

H1.text: Life cycle is the pattern by which trees start as seeds, grow into mature trees, and produce more seeds.

H2.text: Food supply is the pattern represented by trees that start as seeds and grow into mature trees that produce more seeds.

H3.text: Life span is the pattern in which trees start as seeds and grow into mature trees that produce more seeds.

A4.text: Biological life cycle, the sequence of life stages that an organism undergoes from conception to reproduction

A5.text: Enterprise life cycle, the process of changing a business enterprise

A6.text: The mature sporophyte produces haploid spores by meiosis, a process which reduces the number of chromosomes to half, from two sets to one.

A7.text: Two single-celled haploid gametes, each containing n unpaired chromosomes, fuse to form a single-celled diploid zygote, which now contains 2n (paired) chromosomes.
